{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:27:00.508635+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6ebc2af79b91200a02d42f2ee044c6196927972f)", "id": "lc_c3d56ade-f6e0-4535-b3b5-d55588933588"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import React, { useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { useNavigate } from \"react-router-dom\";\nimport { auth } from \"../../config/firebase\";\n\nconst AuthChecker = ({ children }) => {\n  const navigate = useNavigate();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!auth.currentUser) {\n      navigate(\"/login\");\n    }\n  }, []); // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n\n  return <>{children}</>;\n};\n\nexport default AuthChecker;\n", "id": "lc_4833eea4-7407-4cee-94b7-156b96b97407"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "5d850377-350f-4e81-91e5-7d7f72feb796", "tool_call_id": "call_00_eRZRVPAjft3SY7odJnV23529", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:27:03.093027+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 113, "prompt_tokens": 7643, "total_tokens": 7756, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 24, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7424}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 7424, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 219}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "7dc09502-bab3-4b8b-901b-6a56be257ac0", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea57b-e41d-7f50-b725-ee6348d2a0ee-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T02_R02_C02_A03", "path": "README.md"}, "id": "call_00_Ckse7FI9g4KmVmBVMJxM1905", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7643, "output_tokens": 113, "total_tokens": 7756, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7424}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 24}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:27:04.111955+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: df190a3d1305b893e016cf1bacb81be32b01c4f0)", "id": "lc_af0aef2e-5f08-42ac-a25a-5a484100ed21"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<div align=\"center\">\n\n# Create React App Firebase Starter Template\n\n[![npm](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/cra-template-firebase-starter.svg)](https://npmjs.com/package/cra-template-firebase-starter)\n[![npm](https://img.shields.io/npm/dy/cra-template-firebase-starter.svg)](https://npmjs.com/package/cra-template-firebase-starter)\n[![License MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-orange.svg?style=flat)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pettiboy/cra-template-firebase-starter/main/LICENSE)\n[![PRs Welcome](https://img.shields.io/badge/PRs-Welcome-brightgreen.svg)](https://github.com/pettiboy/cra-template-firebase-starter/pulls)\n\n![React](https://img.shields.io/badge/React-20232A?style=for-the-badge&logo=react&logoColor=61DAFB)\n![NPM](https://img.shields.io/badge/npm-CB3837?style=for-the-badge&logo=npm&logoColor=white)\n\nMake sure you ⭐️ this [`repository`](https://github.com/pettiboy/cra-template-firebase-starter) if you find it helpful or interesting :)\n\n</div>\n\n## ✨ Installation\n\n```bash\nnpx create-react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\nOR\n\n```bash\nyarn create react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\n`NOTE:` This `template` is also available in `TypeScript` [here](https://github.com/pettiboy/cra-template-typescript-firebase).\n\n## ⚙️ Usage\n\n### SetUp firebase\n\n1. Go to your [`Firebase Console`](https://console.firebase.google.com/)\n\n2. Click on `Add project`.\n\n   - Follow steps and create project.\n\n3. Click on web icon.\n\n   - Register web app.\n   - You will get details for setting up `Firebase SDK`.\n\n4. Add the config details in your `.env` file (available in root of your project).\n\n### SetUp SignIn with google\n\n1. In your project console, click on `Authentication` and `Get Started`.\n\n2. In `Sign-in method`, click on `Google`.\n\n3. Toggle `Enable` and click on `Save`.\n\n### To create a new screen\n\n1. Create a new component in `src/screens`.\n\n2. In your `src/config/routes.ts`.\n\n```js\n{\n    path: \"/your-route\",\n    component: YourScreenComponentName,\n    name: \"Screen Name For Reference\",\n    protected: false, // if user needs to be authenticated to access this screen\n}\n```\n\n### To Deploy on GitHub Pages\n\n1. Add your domain (your-github-username.github.io) to the OAuth redirect domains list in the `Firebase console -> Auth section -> Sign in method tab`.\n\n2. update the `homepage` field in your `package.json` to the domain you are hosting on. (By default it is: `http://your-github-username.github.io/your-repo-name`)\n\n3. (Optional) Test production build locally: Update the `homepage` field to `/` and run:\n\n```bash\nnpm i -g serve # install serve globally via npm\nnpm run build-and-serve\n```\n\n4. Deploy to GitHub Pages run:\n\n```bash\nnpm run deploy\n```\n\n## ✨ Featues\n\n### 1. Routing\n\nRouting setup using `react-router-dom`.\n\n- With easily implementable private routes (routes only authenticated users can use).\n\n- Easily add new screens.\n\n### 2. Authentication\n\nAuthentication implemented implemented\n\nSignIn with Google implemented using `firebase` and `react-firebase-hooks`.\n\n### 3. Firebase Configured\n\nFirebase configured with `GoogleAuthProvider` implemented.\n\n### 4. Material UI\n\nLogin Screen UI built using `@mui/material`.\n\n### 5. Deploy on Github Pages\n\nDeploying on GitHub pages powered by `gh-pages` and [`spa-github-pages`](https://github.com/rafgraph/spa-github-pages)\n\n## 🔧 File Structure\n\n```\n├── src\n│   ├── components\n│   │   ├── auth\n│   │   |   ├── AuthChecker.js\n│   │   |   ├── AuthContainer.js\n│   │   |   ├── Logout.js\n│   │   ├── utils\n│   │   |   ├── Center.js\n│   ├── config\n│   │   ├── firebase.config.js\n│   │   ├── firebase.js\n│   │   ├── routes.js\n│   ├── screens\n│   │   ├── Login.js\n│   │   ├── Home.js\n```\n\n## 📝 Authors\n\n- Hussain Pettiwala ([@pettiboy](https://github.com/pettiboy))\n\nSpecial thanks to this well written [`blog`](https://grischuk.de/how-to-create-custom-create-react-app-cra-templates) and this [`repo`](https://github.com/alexandr-g/cra-template-typescript-redux) by [alexandr-g](https://github.com/alexandr-g).\n", "id": "lc_feb33279-681a-4751-9170-6482be943f14"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "59848f26-f5ed-4432-9fc6-9e2d9af12de1", "tool_call_id": "call_00_Ckse7FI9g4KmVmBVMJxM1905", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:27:24.700760+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a complete picture of the routing setup. Here's my analysis:\n\n---\n\n## How Routing Is Configured\n\nThis is a **React** app using **react-router-dom v6**. The routing follows a declarative, configuration-driven pattern spread across two main files:\n\n### 1. Route Definitions — `src/config/routes.js`\n\nA plain JavaScript array of route objects, each with:\n- `path` — the URL path\n- `component` — the React component to render\n- `name` — a human-readable label\n- `protected` — a boolean flag indicating whether the route should be guarded\n\n```js\nconst routes = [\n  { path: \"\",         component: Home,  name: \"Home Page\",   protected: true  },\n  { path: \"/login\",   component: Login, name: \"Login Screen\", protected: false },\n];\n```\n\n### 2. Route Rendering — `src/App.js`\n\nA single `<Routes>` block iterates over the array. For each route, it inspects the `protected` flag:\n- If **`protected: true`**, the component is wrapped in `<AuthChecker>`, which verifies that a Firebase user is logged in.\n- If **`protected: false`**, the component is rendered directly without any guard.\n\n```js\n<Routes>\n  {routes.map((route, index) => (\n    <Route\n      key={index}\n      path={route.path}\n      element={\n        route.protected ? (\n          <AuthChecker><route.component /></AuthChecker>\n        ) : (\n          <route.component />\n        )\n      }\n    />\n  ))}\n</Routes>\n```\n\n### 3. Auth Guard — `src/components/auth/AuthChecker.js`\n\n`AuthChecker` reads the current Firebase user (`auth.currentUser`). If no user is found, it immediately redirects to `/login` via `useNavigate()`. Otherwise, it renders its children (the protected page).\n\n---\n\n## Which Route Requires Authentication and Which Is Public\n\n| Route       | Path       | `protected` Flag | Access       |\n|-------------|------------|------------------|--------------|\n| **Home**    | `/` (root) | `true`           | 🔒 **Requires authentication** (guarded by `AuthChecker`) |\n| **Login**   | `/login`   | `false`          | 🌐 **Public** (no auth required) |\n\n- The **Home** page is the protected route — an unauthenticated user is redirected to `/login`.\n- The **Login** page is the public route — anyone can access it to sign in.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1429, "prompt_tokens": 8922, "total_tokens": 10351, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 889, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7680}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 7680, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 1242}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "ad93abfa-07fa-47f2-930d-f7e354560562", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea57b-f230-71d0-80a1-036d00f1899c-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8922, "output_tokens": 1429, "total_tokens": 10351, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7680}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 889}}}}]}}}
